Samuel Awoyinfa Bajaj Auto Limited and its distribution partner in Nigeria, DAG Motorcycles Limited have opened 28 camps across the country to offer repair services to patrons of its three-wheeler and two-wheeler automobiles. The company had recently stormed major cities across the country to offer free service/checkup camps for the three-wheeler owners and riders. A statement from the company on Thursday said the 28 camps where the company opened service centres included Abuja, Jos, Minna and Suleja. Other cities in the list included Nasarawa, Sokoto, Kebbi, Bauchi, Jigawa, Yobe, Adamawa and Borno, Kano, Zaria and Kaduna and Lagos. The statement said the company which is reputed to be the world’s largest manufacturer of three-wheeler and two-wheeler automobiles placed much value on the Nigerian market. It said, “Manufacturers all over the world have gone beyond just producing and selling their products. They now provide consumers and customers with value-added services. “Nigeria is a very important market for us and that is why we are working tirelessly to come up with products to serve the various needs of its people.” The company emphasised its commitment to expand its presence in Nigeria by making life simpler for customers through innovating more technologically-powered products. Copyright PUNCH.
